efore 18 July 1558":"about 1530–before 18 July 1558","1529–1559":"1529–1559","1549–1616":"1549–1616","1551–1616":"1551–1616","1553–1609":"1553–1609","1555–1616":"1555–1616","1530–1558":"1530–1558","before July 1558":"before July 1558","1558":"1558","about 1549":"about 1549","1555":"1555","about 1548":"about 1548","1553":"1553","1530":"1530","1551":"1551","1609":"1609","about 1530":"about 1530","about 1553":"about 1553","1529":"1529","about 1551":"about 1551","1616":"1616","1549":"1549","before 18 July 1558":"before 18 July 1558","1559":"1559","Royston, Hertfordshire, England":"Royston, Hertfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Foote","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: from Middle English <i>fot</i> ‘foot’ (Old English <i>fōt</i>), sometimes translated in medieval documents by Latin <i>cum pede</i> ‘with the foot’. Probably a nickname for someone with a deformity of the foot or with large feet.","English: occasionally perhaps from the rare Middle English personal name <i>Fot</i>, from Old Norse <i>Fótr</i>, originally a nickname with the same sense as 1 above.","English: topographic name for someone who lived at the foot of a hill."],"variants":[{"name":"Foot","meanings":["English: variant of   Foote  .","North German: from Middle Low German <i>vōt</i> ‘foot’; probably a nickname for someone with some peculiarity or deformity of the foot."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":19,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":28,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"John Foote was born about 1530, in Royston, Hertfordshire, England. He married Helen Warren alias Waller about 1548, in Royston, Hertfordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. In 1558, his occupation is listed as tallow chandler in Royston, Hertfordshire, England. He died before 18 July 1558, in his hometown."},"et":{"about 1530–before 18 July 1558":"umbes 1530–enne 18. juulit 1558","1529–1559":"1529–1559","1549–1616":"1549–1616","1551–1616":"1551–1616","1553–1609":"1553–1609","1555–1616":"1555–1616","1530–1558":"1530–1558","before July 1558":"enne juulit 1558","1558":"1558","about 1549":"umbes 1549","1555":"1555","about 1548":"umbes 1548","1553":"1553","1530":"1530","1551":"1551","1609":"1609","about 1530":"umbes 1530","about 1553":"umbes 1553","1529":"1529","about 1551":"umbes 1551","1616":"1616","1549":"1549","before 18 July 1558":"enne 18. juulit 1558","1559":"1559","Royston, Hertfordshire, England":"Royston, Hertfordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1530–before 18 July 1558":"noin 1530–ennen vuotta 18. heinäkuuta 1558","1529–1559":"1529–1559","1549–1616":"1549–1616","1551–1616":"1551–1616","1553–1609":"1553–1609","1555–1616":"1555–1616","1530–1558":"1530–1558","before July 1558":"ennen v